description: {"blocks":[{"key":"bu2oc","text":"This protocol is for isolation and transfection of primary hepatocytes from Atlantic salmon. We have confirmed plasmid transfection efficiency of up to 46% and RNP cutting efficiency up to 60%. Primary cells can survive in culture for at least three weeks, with transgene expression 48 hours post transfection. We find that coating of culture plates with polyethylenimine (PEI) is essential to cell adhesion.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
